#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Dasabalavagga"
msgstr "3. The Ten Powers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Bhūmijasutta"
msgstr "25. With Bhūmija"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.38"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.25:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā bhūmijo sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā "
"sāriputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā sāriputtena saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Bhūmija came out of retreat, went to "
"Venerable Sāriputta, and exchanged greetings with him."

msgctxt "sn12.25:1.3"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho āyasmā bhūmijo āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Santāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"“Reverend Sāriputta, there are ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy "
"of deeds. Some of them declare that pleasure and pain are made by oneself."

msgctxt "sn12.25:2.2"
msgid ""
"Santi panāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā paraṅkataṃ "
"sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr "Some of them declare that pleasure and pain are made by another."

msgctxt "sn12.25:2.3"
msgid ""
"Santāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkatañca paraṅkatañca "
"sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"Some of them declare that pleasure and pain are made by both oneself and "
"another."

msgctxt "sn12.25:2.4"
msgid ""
"Santi panāvuso sāriputta, eke samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ "
"aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti."
msgstr ""
"Some of them declare that pleasure and pain arise by chance, not made by "
"oneself or another."

msgctxt "sn12.25:2.5"
msgid "Idha no, āvuso sāriputta, bhagavā kiṃvādī kimakkhāyī, "
msgstr "What does the Buddha say about this? How does he explain it? "

msgctxt "sn12.25:2.6"
msgid ""
"kathaṃ byākaramānā ca mayaṃ vuttavādino ceva bhagavato assāma, na ca "
"bhagavantaṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyyāma, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyyāma, "
"na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"How should we answer so as to repeat what the Buddha has said, and not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth? How should we explain in line with his "
"teaching, with no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:3.1"
msgid "“Paṭiccasamuppannaṃ kho, āvuso, sukhadukkhaṃ vuttaṃ bhagavatā."
msgstr "“Reverend, the Buddha said that suffering is dependently originated."

msgctxt "sn12.25:3.2"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca?"
msgstr "Dependent on what?"

msgctxt "sn12.25:3.3"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca."
msgstr "Dependent on contact."

msgctxt "sn12.25:3.4"
msgid ""
"Iti vadaṃ vuttavādī ceva bhagavato assa, na ca bhagavantaṃ abhūtena "
"abbhācikkheyya, dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko "
"vādānupāto gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"If you said this you would repeat what the Buddha has said, and not "
"misrepresent him with an untruth. You would explain in line with his "
"teaching, and there would be no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti, tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the "
"case of those who declare that pleasure and pain are made by oneself, that’s "
"conditioned by contact. …"

msgctxt "sn12.25:4.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:4.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:4.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti, tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that pleasure and pain arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another, that’s also conditioned by contact."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.39"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrāvuso, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the "
"case of those who declare that pleasure and pain are made by oneself, it’s "
"impossible that they will experience that without contact."

msgctxt "sn12.25:5.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:5.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:5.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ "
"ṭhānaṃ vijjatī”ti."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that pleasure and pain arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another, it’s impossible that they will experience that "
"without contact.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:6.1"
msgid ""
"Assosi kho āyasmā ānando āyasmato sāriputtassa āyasmatā bhūmijena saddhiṃ "
"imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Venerable Ānanda heard this discussion between Venerable Sāriputta and "
"Venerable Bhūmija."

msgctxt "sn12.25:6.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side,"

msgctxt "sn12.25:6.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando yāvatako āyasmato sāriputtassa āyasmatā "
"bhūmijena saddhiṃ ahosi kathāsallāpo taṃ sabbaṃ bhagavato ārocesi."
msgstr "and informed the Buddha of all they had discussed."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:7.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, ānanda, yathā taṃ sāriputto sammā byākaramāno byākareyya."
msgstr "“Good, good, Ānanda! It’s just as Sāriputta has so rightly explained."

msgctxt "sn12.25:7.2"
msgid "Paṭiccasamuppannaṃ kho, ānanda, sukhadukkhaṃ vuttaṃ mayā."
msgstr "I have said that pleasure and pain are dependently originated."

msgctxt "sn12.25:7.3"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca?"
msgstr "Dependent on what?"

msgctxt "sn12.25:7.4"
msgid "Phassaṃ paṭicca."
msgstr "Dependent on contact."

msgctxt "sn12.25:7.5"
msgid ""
"Iti vadaṃ vuttavādī ceva me assa, na ca maṃ abhūtena abbhācikkheyya, "
"dhammassa cānudhammaṃ byākareyya, na ca koci sahadhammiko vādānupāto "
"gārayhaṃ ṭhānaṃ āgaccheyya."
msgstr ""
"Saying this you would repeat what I have said, and not misrepresent me with "
"an untruth. You would explain in line with my teaching, and there would be "
"no legitimate grounds for rebuke and criticism."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:8.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the "
"case of those who declare that pleasure and pain are made by oneself, that’s "
"conditioned by contact. …"

msgctxt "sn12.25:8.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:8.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:8.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti tadapi phassapaccayā."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that pleasure and pain arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another, that’s also conditioned by contact."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:9.1"
msgid ""
"Tatrānanda, ye te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā sayaṅkataṃ sukhadukkhaṃ "
"paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"Consider the ascetics and brahmins who teach the efficacy of deeds. In the "
"case of those who declare that pleasure and pain are made by oneself, it’s "
"impossible that they will experience that without contact."

msgctxt "sn12.25:9.2"
msgid "Yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:9.3"
msgid "yepi te … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:9.4"
msgid ""
"yepi te samaṇabrāhmaṇā kammavādā asayaṅkāraṃ aparaṅkāraṃ adhiccasamuppannaṃ "
"sukhadukkhaṃ paññapenti, te vata aññatra phassā paṭisaṃvedissantīti netaṃ "
"ṭhānaṃ vijjati."
msgstr ""
"In the case of those who declare that pleasure and pain arise by chance, not "
"made by oneself or another, it’s impossible that they will experience that "
"without contact."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.40"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:10.1"
msgid ""
"Kāye vā hānanda, sati kāyasañcetanāhetu uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, as long as there’s a body, the intention that gives rise to "
"bodily action causes pleasure and pain to arise in oneself."

msgctxt "sn12.25:10.2"
msgid ""
"Vācāya vā hānanda, sati vacīsañcetanāhetu uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"As long as there’s a voice, the intention that gives rise to verbal action "
"causes pleasure and pain to arise in oneself."

msgctxt "sn12.25:10.3"
msgid ""
"Mane vā hānanda, sati manosañcetanāhetu uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ "
"avijjāpaccayā ca."
msgstr ""
"As long as there’s a mind, the intention that gives rise to mental action "
"causes pleasure and pain to arise in oneself. But these only apply when "
"conditioned by ignorance."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
#. VAR: yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ → yaṃpaccayāyataṃ (s1-3, km) | yaṃpaccayā yaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn12.25:11.1"
msgid ""
"Sāmaṃ vā taṃ, ānanda, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"By oneself one instigates the choice that gives rise to bodily, verbal, and "
"mental action, conditioned by which that pleasure and pain arise in oneself."

#. VAR: Pare vā taṃ → parevāssa taṃ (bj, pts1-2) | pare vāyataṃ (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn12.25:11.2"
msgid ""
"Pare vā taṃ, ānanda, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharonti, yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr "Or else others instigate the choice …"

msgctxt "sn12.25:11.3"
msgid ""
"Sampajāno vā taṃ, ānanda, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr "One consciously instigates the choice …"

msgctxt "sn12.25:11.4"
msgid ""
"Asampajāno vā taṃ, ānanda, kāyasaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr "Or else one unconsciously instigates the choice …"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:12.1"
msgid ""
"Sāmaṃ vā taṃ, ānanda, vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:12.2"
msgid ""
"Pare vā taṃ, ānanda, vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharonti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:12.3"
msgid "Sampajāno vā taṃ, ānanda … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:12.4"
msgid ""
"asampajāno vā taṃ, ānanda, vacīsaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:13.1"
msgid ""
"Sāmaṃ vā taṃ, ānanda, manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:13.2"
msgid ""
"Pare vā taṃ, ānanda, manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharonti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:13.3"
msgid "Sampajāno vā taṃ, ānanda … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn12.25:13.4"
msgid ""
"asampajāno vā taṃ, ānanda, manosaṅkhāraṃ abhisaṅkharoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.41"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.25:14.1"
msgid "Imesu, ānanda, dhammesu avijjā anupatitā."
msgstr "Ignorance is included in all these things."

msgctxt "sn12.25:14.2"
msgid ""
"Avijjāya tveva, ānanda, asesavirāganirodhā so kāyo na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ. Sā vācā na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ. So mano na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ "
"uppajjati ajjhattaṃ sukhadukkhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"But when ignorance fades away and ceases with nothing left over, there is no "
"body and no voice and no mind, conditioned by which that pleasure and pain "
"arise in oneself."

msgctxt "sn12.25:14.3"
msgid ""
"Khettaṃ taṃ na hoti … pe … vatthu taṃ na hoti … pe … āyatanaṃ taṃ na hoti … "
"pe … adhikaraṇaṃ taṃ na hoti yaṃpaccayāssa taṃ uppajjati ajjhattaṃ "
"sukhadukkhan”ti."
msgstr ""
"There is no field, no ground, no scope, no basis, conditioned by which that "
"pleasure and pain arise in oneself.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.25:14.4"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
